WEBVTT

00:10.658 --> 00:11.279
Hey, everyone.

00:11.319 --> 00:14.565
First off, I want to say happy Mother's Day.

00:14.605 --> 00:25.906
I've always been so appreciative of mothers, but I feel like especially during this season where I've been working from home, my gratitude has increased.

00:25.986 --> 00:36.883
I'm typically sitting at our dining room table kind of zoned in, focused, but I can see in my periphery just all the things that my wife is doing as a mom to our kids.

00:37.063 --> 00:39.287
And it just makes me so grateful.

00:39.427 --> 00:43.453
So for those of you who are moms, I want to say we love you.

00:43.474 --> 00:46.759
We are so grateful for you and we're praying for you.

00:47.400 --> 00:53.970
And while today is a day to celebrate moms, we also want to acknowledge that it's a hard day for many people.

00:54.082 --> 00:55.504
for a variety of reasons.

00:55.885 --> 01:07.302
And because of that, we've made it a tradition to read this poem every year that really captures the complexity of this day and reminds us that we're all in this together.

01:07.442 --> 01:10.006
So I'd like to read this to you all.

01:11.669 --> 01:16.316
To those who gave birth this year to their first child, we celebrate with you.

01:17.277 --> 01:20.562
To those who lost a child this year, we mourn with you.

01:21.538 --> 01:27.388
To those who are in the trenches with little ones every day and where the badge of food stains, we appreciate you.

01:29.271 --> 01:35.561
To those who experienced loss this year through miscarriage, failed adoptions or running away, we mourn with you.

01:36.883 --> 01:43.374
To those who walk the hard path of infertility, fraught with pokes, prods, tears and disappointment, we walk with you.

01:44.255 --> 01:45.958
Forgive us when we say foolish things.

01:46.098 --> 01:48.242
We don't mean to make this harder than it is.

01:49.122 --> 01:53.827
To those who are foster moms, mentor moms, and spiritual moms, we need you.

01:55.309 --> 02:00.334
To those who have warm and close relationships with your children, we celebrate with you.

02:02.196 --> 02:07.102
To those who have disappointment, heartache, and distance with your children, we sit with you.

02:08.623 --> 02:11.867
To those who lost their mothers this year, we grieve with you.

02:13.028 --> 02:18.354
To those who experienced abuse at the hands of your own mother, we acknowledge your experience.

02:19.298 --> 02:26.306
To those who lived through driving tests, medical tests, and the overall testing of motherhood, we are better for having you in our midst.

02:27.607 --> 02:33.013
To all those who have empty your nests in the upcoming year, we grieve and rejoice with you.

02:34.114 --> 02:39.260
And to those who are pregnant with new life, both expected and surprising, we anticipate with you.

02:40.241 --> 02:42.323
This Mother's Day, we walk with you.

02:43.224 --> 02:47.189
Mothering is not for the faint of heart, and we have real warriors in our midst.

02:47.669 --> 02:48.530
We remember you.

02:49.666 --> 02:59.016
So I want to say again, just how thankful I am for the mothers in our church and we want to celebrate you and honor you this day.

03:00.197 --> 03:06.304
All right, before we get to the preaching of the word today, I want to take a minute to talk about the offering.

03:07.305 --> 03:10.769
This is a difficult time financially for a lot of people.

03:11.409 --> 03:17.196
And yet it's been so encouraging to hear about the many ways that people are taking care of each other and helping out.

03:17.936 --> 03:19.538
And the church is a family.

03:19.618 --> 03:20.639
And that's what families do.

03:20.699 --> 03:21.820
We take care of one another.

03:22.281 --> 03:27.607
So I want to encourage you to keep letting your needs be known and then to help each other out.

03:28.267 --> 03:31.511
I also want to encourage you to continue to give to the church.

03:32.332 --> 03:36.616
So much has changed during this time, but it's not like we as a staff are doing less.

03:37.017 --> 03:40.380
We're just focusing all of our attention specifically on a few things.

03:41.081 --> 03:45.166
I mean, in the last week, we fed over 1500 meals at the Hope Center.

03:46.327 --> 03:49.170
We have money set aside in our budget every year.

03:49.666 --> 03:52.830
that we give specifically to people who are in need in the church.

03:52.931 --> 03:55.734
And we've increased that and have helped out so many people.

03:55.774 --> 03:58.238
So when you give to the church, you're helping with that as well.

03:59.079 --> 04:06.469
We're focusing on supporting community groups and our Sunday gatherings as ways of really staying connected during this time.

04:06.609 --> 04:13.038
So there's so much work to be done and there's so much work that is being done and God's using it all for his glory.

04:13.459 --> 04:16.583
So if you want to give the way to do that is through the push pay app.

04:16.663 --> 04:18.546
If you have a smartphone, you can download it

04:19.010 --> 04:22.314
there and then just search for reality LA and set it up on there.

04:22.795 --> 04:24.837
And thank you so much for your generosity.

04:25.278 --> 04:32.687
When we give and when we sacrifice, it shows God's generosity and his sacrifice to this city.

04:33.368 --> 04:38.655
All right, if you've got a Bible, go ahead and grab it and open up to the book of Philippians.

04:39.115 --> 04:42.519
We're in a series right now that we're calling Defiant Joy.

04:42.700 --> 04:47.826
This is teaching us how to live in the midst of this pandemic that we're in right now.

04:47.938 --> 04:54.687
And so today I'm going to be reading from and preaching on Philippians chapter 1, verses 18 through 26.

04:54.927 --> 04:58.672
So I'll read the text for us and then I'll open our time in prayer.

04:59.593 --> 05:01.435
I'll be starting in Philippians 1, 18.

05:01.936 --> 05:04.339
It's just at the latter half of verse 18.

05:06.542 --> 05:08.364
Yes, and I will rejoice.

05:09.286 --> 05:15.794
For I know that through your prayers and the help of the spirit of Jesus Christ, this will turn out for my deliverance.

05:16.514 --> 05:28.327
As it is, my eager expectation and hope that I will not be at all ashamed, but that with full courage now as always, Christ will be honored in my body, whether by life or by death.

05:29.348 --> 05:33.772
For to me, to live is Christ and to die is gain.

05:34.773 --> 05:37.877
If I am to live in the flesh, that means fruitful labor for me.

05:37.937 --> 05:41.100
Yet which I shall choose, I cannot tell.

05:41.240 --> 05:42.962
I am hard pressed between the two.

05:43.458 --> 05:50.346
My desire is to depart and to be with Christ for that is far better, but to remain in the flesh is more necessary on your account.

05:51.188 --> 06:06.146
Convince of this, I know that I will remain and continue with you all for your progress and joy in the faith so that in me, you may have ample cause to glory in Christ Jesus because of my coming to you again."

06:07.067 --> 06:07.848
This is God's Word.

06:08.389 --> 06:09.009
Let's pray together.

06:11.272 --> 06:12.754
God, we come before you.

06:14.690 --> 06:24.261
asking that you would intervene in our lives at a time where everything feels so disorienting and confusing and there's a lot of frustration and loss.

06:24.862 --> 06:34.633
God, we look to you and we thank you that you have spoken that your word pierces the silence and gives us direction and gives us hope.

06:35.354 --> 06:39.478
And so Lord, would you speak today through your word as it's preached?

06:39.498 --> 06:42.802
Would your spirit be at work in our hearts, God?

06:43.266 --> 06:45.630
We ask this in Jesus' name, amen.

06:47.593 --> 06:59.332
Well, in his biography of Steve Jobs, Walter Isaacson tells of a conversation between the two of them where they were sitting in Steve Jobs' backyard in his garden and began discussing life and death.

07:00.174 --> 07:07.466
Steve Jobs said this, sometimes I believe in God, sometimes I don't.

07:08.207 --> 07:09.970
I think it's 50-50 maybe.

07:10.562 --> 07:13.866
But ever since I've had cancer, I've been thinking about it more.

07:14.526 --> 07:16.489
And I find myself believing a bit more.

07:17.289 --> 07:23.056
Maybe it's because I want to believe in an afterlife that when you die, it doesn't just all disappear.

07:23.837 --> 07:26.820
The wisdom you've accumulated, somehow it lives on.

07:28.001 --> 07:35.810
Then he paused for a second and went on and said this, but sometimes I think it's just like an on off switch.

07:36.110 --> 07:37.492
Click and you're gone.

07:38.453 --> 07:39.474
He paused again.

07:40.066 --> 07:45.473
And then he said, and that's why I don't like putting on off switches on Apple devices.

07:47.014 --> 07:53.743
See, the reality of death makes us think about what really matters in life.

07:53.763 --> 07:58.368
But like Steve Jobs, many people in our culture try to avoid thinking about death.

07:58.869 --> 07:59.850
We don't talk about death.

07:59.870 --> 08:00.831
We don't think about death.

08:01.091 --> 08:04.155
We certainly often don't live in light of death.

08:05.116 --> 08:09.842
See, we live in a culture that in general avoids death as much as possible.

08:10.498 --> 08:14.384
But right now, death is staring us in the face.

08:15.746 --> 08:21.615
Right now, I mean, there's been over 70,000 deaths in the United States due to COVID-19.

08:22.416 --> 08:28.785
And in LA County, we've been averaging around 75 deaths per day due to the virus.

08:29.947 --> 08:37.458
And while thankfully no one in our church has died due to COVID-19, many of us, if not most of us, know someone who has.

08:38.690 --> 08:42.016
See, death makes us think about what matters most in life.

08:43.038 --> 08:51.293
And in the book of Philippians, Paul is in prison awaiting his execution, and yet he stares death in the face and doesn't flinch.

08:52.215 --> 08:52.977
And how can he do that?

08:53.858 --> 08:58.066
Because he has a joy that is not determined by his circumstances.

08:58.530 --> 09:04.417
It's not determined by any circumstances, whether you're rich or poor, healthy or sick, hungry or fed.

09:04.737 --> 09:05.458
It doesn't matter.

09:05.798 --> 09:12.726
This joy transcends all circumstances, even as we'll see in Philippians 1, life and death.

09:13.908 --> 09:18.893
So let's walk through this passage and see how it can give us direction for today.

09:19.835 --> 09:24.980
Look at the end of verse 18, once again, where we started off.

09:25.041 --> 09:26.322
He simply says yes.

09:26.434 --> 09:29.919
And I will rejoice."

09:29.939 --> 09:30.439
There it is.

09:30.479 --> 09:32.823
That defiant joy.

09:33.644 --> 09:37.869
In the previous verses, he was talking about imprisonment and opposition.

09:37.949 --> 09:40.152
And here he's saying, and yet I choose joy.

09:40.933 --> 09:42.676
It's that resilient faith.

09:43.277 --> 09:48.464
The kind of faith that looks at circumstances in the eye and says, you have no power over me.

09:49.465 --> 09:50.226
But let's keep going.

09:50.246 --> 09:52.729
Look at verses 19 and 20.

09:52.789 --> 09:53.330
He says,

09:53.570 --> 10:00.377
For I know that through your prayers and the help of the Spirit of Jesus Christ, this will turn out from my deliverance.

10:00.397 --> 10:12.729
As it is my eager expectation and hope that I will not be at all ashamed, but that with full courage now, as always, Christ will be honored in my body, whether by life or by death.

10:14.070 --> 10:21.618
Now, you see more of this resilience in him when he says, Christ will be honored in my body.

10:21.954 --> 10:23.015
I love that.

10:23.035 --> 10:25.618
It's not up to him, whether he's in prison or not.

10:26.158 --> 10:27.700
But he says, here's what I know.

10:27.780 --> 10:31.263
No matter what happens, Christ is going to be honored in my life.

10:32.244 --> 10:38.951
And I think this is a good word for us because we often spend so much of our energy on things that we can't control.

10:40.172 --> 10:42.394
But I want to remind you that you can choose today.

10:42.454 --> 10:46.859
I'm going to live for the glory of Jesus, no matter what comes my way.

10:48.240 --> 10:50.002
Now in verse 19,

10:50.338 --> 10:52.162
He talked about his deliverance.

10:52.262 --> 10:55.428
And he says, I know that this deliverance is coming.

10:55.468 --> 10:59.837
And when you heard that, you might have assumed that he's talking about getting out of prison.

11:00.879 --> 11:06.710
But the word that he uses for deliverance here is actually the same word that's translated salvation.

11:06.750 --> 11:10.738
It's a term that's often used for ultimate deliverance.

11:11.298 --> 11:22.274
And we know he's not merely talking about being delivered from prison here because he says in the next verse, Christ will be honored in my body, whether by death or by life.

11:23.355 --> 11:30.105
So it's like he's saying, whether I get delivered out of prison or get delivered into eternal life, I'm going to get delivered.

11:31.367 --> 11:33.610
It reminds me of a story I heard recently.

11:33.790 --> 11:35.492
It comes from Tony Evans.

11:35.553 --> 11:36.594
Tony Evans is

11:36.674 --> 11:38.997
one of my all-time favorite preachers.

11:39.017 --> 11:43.724
He's an African-American preacher from the South and he just preaches the lights out.

11:43.764 --> 11:44.986
I love Tony Evans.

11:45.647 --> 11:51.075
But this past year, Dr. Evans' wife tragically passed away.

11:52.156 --> 12:00.568
And I watched the funeral service online and his son, Jonathan Evans spoke about his mother.

12:01.430 --> 12:04.434
And he spoke about wrestling with God

12:04.802 --> 12:06.625
about not answering his prayers.

12:06.745 --> 12:10.751
He had been praying for his mom's healing and that didn't happen.

12:11.672 --> 12:21.928
But he said that it was as if the Lord then said to him, just because I didn't answer your prayer your way doesn't mean I didn't answer your prayer anyway.

12:22.849 --> 12:30.461
And then God said to him, because of the victory that I've given you, there's always only two answers to your prayers.

12:31.603 --> 12:33.906
Either she was gonna be healed

12:34.306 --> 12:35.508
or she was gonna be healed.

12:36.349 --> 12:39.633
Either she was gonna live or she was gonna live.

12:40.193 --> 12:43.858
Either she was gonna be with family or she was gonna be with family.

12:44.259 --> 12:48.564
Either she was gonna be well taken care of or she was gonna be well taken care of.

12:49.205 --> 12:55.052
See, victory belongs to the Lord and that's true in life and in death.

12:56.814 --> 13:02.962
And so for Paul, this confidence in God's deliverance in death or life

13:03.554 --> 13:06.338
It leads to this hypothetical dilemma.

13:06.638 --> 13:09.182
So let me read you verses 21 through 24.

13:09.603 --> 13:18.736
As we see this dilemma that he presents, verse 21, for to me to live is Christ and to die as gain.

13:19.577 --> 13:22.361
If I am to live in the flesh, that means fruitful labor for me.

13:22.401 --> 13:24.264
Yet which shall I choose?

13:24.344 --> 13:25.065
I cannot tell.

13:25.085 --> 13:27.308
I am hard pressed between the two.

13:27.529 --> 13:29.632
My desire is to depart and be with Christ.

13:30.113 --> 13:31.154
For that is far better.

13:31.554 --> 13:35.518
but to remain in the flesh is more necessary on your account.

13:36.299 --> 13:49.954
So think about his situation here, Paul's in prison awaiting death, and he's asking this hypothetical question, would I rather die and go and be with the Lord or stay and continue the mission he's called me to?

13:50.915 --> 13:57.202
But they're both great options in his mind to live his Christ, to die his gain.

13:57.794 --> 13:59.776
And I want you to think about both of these a little bit.

13:59.796 --> 14:02.480
First of all, he says, to live is Christ.

14:03.401 --> 14:04.862
What a way to describe life.

14:05.203 --> 14:06.064
I mean, think about this.

14:06.124 --> 14:12.291
Remember, he's in chains, but he's saying, my life is not defined by my context, but by my king.

14:13.012 --> 14:13.793
And he has risen.

14:14.614 --> 14:17.397
So he can say, to live is Christ.

14:17.437 --> 14:19.780
He's saying, if I got Jesus, I got all I need.

14:21.082 --> 14:24.786
But while he says to live is Christ, he also says, to die is gain.

14:25.570 --> 14:31.857
Here at the Apostle Paul in this rat infested cold prison, it is longing for eternity.

14:31.917 --> 14:42.348
He's longing for what he knows is guaranteed because of the gospel that evil will be eradicated, that all injustice will be put to an end.

14:42.929 --> 14:52.078
He's longing for the day when there's no more suffering, when every tear will be wiped away and he's in the full presence of God.

14:53.460 --> 14:55.442
See, most people fear death.

14:56.194 --> 15:01.843
But Paul's not afraid of death because he knows that death is a doorway to eternal life.

15:03.646 --> 15:15.205
This confidence that he has reminds me of the same kind of confidence, confidence that I heard of a story of another believer hundreds of years after in the fourth century.

15:15.926 --> 15:20.754
John Chrysostom was a great preacher and a theologian in the early church.

15:21.218 --> 15:27.685
But there was a point in his life where he was literally being threatened by the Empress to be banished because of his faith.

15:28.986 --> 15:32.250
And here's what he said in response to this.

15:33.531 --> 15:40.298
This is such an epic passage from John Christostom showing this confidence.

15:40.359 --> 15:44.983
He says, if the Empress wishes to banish me, let her do so.

15:45.024 --> 15:46.425
The earth is the Lord's.

15:47.206 --> 15:51.090
If she wants to have me saw on a sander, I will have Isaiah for an example.

15:51.522 --> 15:54.547
If she wants me to be drowned in the ocean, I think of Jonah.

15:55.208 --> 15:59.275
If I am to be thrown in the fire, the three men in the furnace suffered the same.

16:00.197 --> 16:03.643
If cast before wild beasts, I remember Daniel in the lion's den.

16:04.424 --> 16:08.010
If she wants me to be stoned, I have before me Stephen, the first martyr.

16:08.571 --> 16:10.574
If she demands my head, let her do so.

16:10.835 --> 16:12.658
John the Baptist shines before me.

16:13.250 --> 16:15.173
Naked, I came from my mother's womb.

16:15.673 --> 16:17.276
Naked, shall I leave this world?

16:17.716 --> 16:23.464
Paul reminds me, if I still pleased men, I would not be the servant of Christ."

16:24.806 --> 16:32.637
What an incredible note of confidence that he has because of what God has done for him in Christ.

16:32.677 --> 16:35.441
I mean, what can you do with a Christian like this?

16:36.162 --> 16:41.970
Paul and Chrysostom, they have this mentality, like, if you beat me, it's going to make me stronger.

16:42.210 --> 16:44.413
If you kill me, I get to go be with Jesus.

16:44.873 --> 16:47.556
If you let me live, I'm gonna preach the gospel to more people.

16:48.498 --> 16:51.041
If you strip me naked, I'm clothed in Christ.

16:51.281 --> 16:53.604
If you take my money, I'm rich in Christ.

16:53.844 --> 16:57.028
If you take my life, Jesus gives me eternal life.

16:58.650 --> 17:06.539
It's as if someone's trying to blow out a fire and yet it stokes the flames even more.

17:06.739 --> 17:09.042
What incredible confidence.

17:10.018 --> 17:16.565
And so I want you to know today that you don't have to be afraid, even of death.

17:17.966 --> 17:25.373
I mean, this may sound a little dramatic, but listen, we're in the midst of a pandemic where so many people are dying.

17:26.354 --> 17:27.856
What if you got the coronavirus?

17:29.497 --> 17:32.600
What if you knew death was coming soon for you?

17:33.802 --> 17:37.185
Here's the thing, we're all going to die eventually.

17:37.225 --> 17:38.226
That's inevitable.

17:39.106 --> 17:47.014
So whether it's this week because of the coronavirus or whether that's decades later, we all have to face death.

17:47.975 --> 17:51.038
And because of the gospel, you don't have to be afraid of it.

17:51.698 --> 17:56.083
You too can say like Paul to live is Christ, but to die is gain.

17:57.304 --> 18:02.749
So Paul presents this hypothetical dilemma, to live as Christ to die is gain.

18:03.690 --> 18:04.771
Which should I choose?

18:05.032 --> 18:07.474
Which should I embrace, so to speak?

18:07.650 --> 18:10.154
And listen to his answer in verse 25.

18:10.194 --> 18:20.328
He says, I know that I will remain and continue with you all for your progress and joy in the faith.

18:21.470 --> 18:24.234
He embraces the mission that God has given him.

18:24.294 --> 18:27.138
He wants to stay and live and why?

18:27.158 --> 18:30.643
Well, in short, because there's still work to be done.

18:30.703 --> 18:32.625
There's still work to be done.

18:33.847 --> 18:35.890
I remember when, when I was a young believer,

18:36.482 --> 18:46.471
And I was at a time where I was struggling and I was just feeling the difficulty of temptation and pain and all the tension and struggle that comes in life.

18:46.552 --> 18:51.506
And I remember thinking, why when I trusted Christ for salvation?

18:51.746 --> 18:54.449
Why does God not just immediately take us to heaven?

18:54.589 --> 19:06.402
Like why not immediately take us out of all this brokenness and pain and hurt and sin and bring us into the fullness of His presence where we experience the fullness of His goodness.

19:06.482 --> 19:10.807
Why doesn't when we trust Christ for salvation, why doesn't He just immediately take us to heaven?

19:11.848 --> 19:13.830
Well, the reason is there's work to be done.

19:14.792 --> 19:16.313
There's a mission that we've been given.

19:16.373 --> 19:20.658
See, God is saving sinners and renewing His creation.

19:21.090 --> 19:26.078
He's doing an incredible work and he's called us to participate in his work.

19:27.601 --> 19:39.300
And so we need to be able to look to Christ knowing that in between the resurrection and the return of Christ, that we have to live in this tension, but we have to remain.

19:39.380 --> 19:41.063
We have to abide in Christ.

19:41.103 --> 19:47.634
We have to continue knowing that we can look forward to that day as glorious as it will be.

19:48.258 --> 19:56.127
And listen, when we experience pain in life, it should make us ache and long for the new creation.

19:56.167 --> 19:57.969
I mean, it's going to be glorious.

19:58.990 --> 19:59.911
We're not going to suffer.

19:59.971 --> 20:03.475
We're going to be in the presence of the Lord and all of His fullness.

20:04.176 --> 20:08.200
We're going to be together every tribe and tongue and people and nation worshiping Christ.

20:08.260 --> 20:12.124
It's going to be amazing, but not yet.

20:12.144 --> 20:14.527
There's work to do.

20:14.567 --> 20:17.170
And so Paul says,

20:18.210 --> 20:25.021
that to live is Christ and that he wants to continue forward with this mission that God has given him.

20:25.041 --> 20:27.605
And so what does he mean when he says to live is Christ?

20:27.645 --> 20:30.450
Well, I think he explains that to us in the text.

20:30.470 --> 20:36.640
So first of all, when he says to live is Christ, he means that it's to live a life of fruitful labor.

20:37.421 --> 20:42.309
So in verse 22, he uses that phrase, fruitful labor.

20:42.349 --> 20:45.714
And I love that because it has a lot of tension built into it.

20:46.338 --> 20:48.501
See, everybody wants fruit, but nobody wants to labor.

20:49.943 --> 20:54.190
We want joy and peace, but we don't want to sacrifice and serve.

20:55.512 --> 21:00.559
But fruit without labor is, it's shallow and it's not lasting.

21:00.579 --> 21:07.890
The fruit won't be very good and it won't keep coming back every season if you don't actually labor and toil and work at it.

21:08.514 --> 21:16.704
But while fruit without labor might be shallow and not lasting, labor without fruit just leads us to despair, working hard and seeing nothing.

21:17.925 --> 21:22.671
But what we see here is to live as Christ is to enter into this tension of fruitful labor.

21:23.372 --> 21:25.495
To know that it's not supposed to be easy.

21:26.956 --> 21:30.501
We live in a fallen world and yet God's doing this beautiful work of redemption.

21:31.061 --> 21:38.290
So I want to call you to embracing that tension, keep going, keep laboring and trusting God to bear fruit.

21:39.266 --> 21:42.971
So to live is Christ means a life of fruitful labor.

21:43.071 --> 21:45.895
It also means a life live for others.

21:46.696 --> 21:55.687
Look at verse 24 where he says that, he says, to remain in the flesh is more necessary on your account.

21:56.648 --> 22:02.236
What I want you to notice is that what makes his decision is not what's best for him, but the wellbeing of others.

22:03.237 --> 22:07.122
He's not driven here by self-preservation, but by love.

22:07.906 --> 22:10.009
Where would Paul get such a mentality?

22:10.970 --> 22:11.951
Jesus, of course.

22:12.792 --> 22:15.395
Jesus is the one who laid down his life for others.

22:16.096 --> 22:20.221
And his call is to deny yourself and follow his way of love.

22:20.801 --> 22:23.124
That's exactly what Paul is doing.

22:23.805 --> 22:27.670
So to live as Christ means a life of fruitful labor, a life lived for others.

22:28.170 --> 22:31.775
And it also means a life lived for joyful progress.

22:32.536 --> 22:34.578
Now look at verse 25.

22:35.266 --> 22:43.619
for this where he specifically says all of this is for your progress and joy in the faith.

22:43.639 --> 22:58.281
Now, I love that he mentions progress and joy right in the same breath here because I think that these are probably in my opinion, the two main themes in the book of Philippians, progress and joy.

22:58.722 --> 23:03.890
But what's absolutely unique is the way that these two come together and are held together

23:04.322 --> 23:08.086
I mean, where else do you see this joy and progress together like this?

23:09.087 --> 23:12.029
And some of you might be thinking that they work together like this.

23:12.090 --> 23:14.412
Well, yeah, there's joy at the end of progress.

23:14.452 --> 23:17.615
Like you work hard and then you get this reward of joy.

23:18.576 --> 23:22.480
But no, what we're seeing here is that joy is not the finish line.

23:22.840 --> 23:26.003
It's the, it's the engine that gets us to the finish line.

23:27.064 --> 23:33.170
Joy compels us and moves us forward to, to make progress.

23:33.506 --> 23:35.648
for the kingdom of God, for the glory of God.

23:36.529 --> 23:42.555
And that's where we then see in Philippians one, that this joy then overflows into praise.

23:42.716 --> 23:51.745
Look at verse 26, he says, all of this, so that in me, you may have ample cause to glory in Christ Jesus.

23:53.247 --> 23:56.510
See, God's glory is not competing with our joy.

23:57.231 --> 24:00.274
Praise is the overflow of our joy.

24:00.834 --> 24:07.442
When we delight in God and thank God and express gratitude and rejoice, that's worship.

24:08.624 --> 24:11.227
And so we choose to worship through these trials.

24:11.968 --> 24:14.211
We choose to praise through this hardship.

24:14.231 --> 24:22.881
We choose to rejoice even in the midst of a pandemic because we see how good God is and how good he's been to us.

24:24.023 --> 24:29.810
And this is where I want to remind you of what our true source of joy is.

24:30.370 --> 24:38.562
We can have a joy beyond circumstances because our joy is rooted in Christ and what he has done for us.

24:39.604 --> 24:43.269
And it's the gospel that's going to bring up this joy.

24:43.349 --> 24:47.816
It's going to cultivate joy in you more and more and more throughout your life.

24:48.978 --> 24:59.794
And so let me remind you, or for maybe some of you, those of you who haven't heard this, let me proclaim this good news of great joy while we were still sinners.

25:00.290 --> 25:10.044
When we rebelled against God and thought we were smarter than him and tried to do things our own way and worked ourselves into a mess, God sent his son for us.

25:11.026 --> 25:13.489
He responded with mercy and love.

25:14.190 --> 25:16.013
And Jesus lived a perfect life.

25:16.914 --> 25:18.216
He was perfectly just.

25:18.717 --> 25:20.079
He was perfectly kind.

25:20.420 --> 25:21.782
He was perfectly loving.

25:21.802 --> 25:24.566
He did everything for the glory of God.

25:25.467 --> 25:27.570
And yet he took that perfect life.

25:27.778 --> 25:31.061
and he offered it up as a sacrifice for us.

25:32.082 --> 25:35.706
Jesus died on the cross, not for himself.

25:36.047 --> 25:37.748
He didn't have any of his own sins.

25:38.409 --> 25:39.530
He died for our sins.

25:39.931 --> 25:41.712
He was our substitute on the cross.

25:41.753 --> 25:48.319
He took our place so that he would bear our judgment so that we could have life.

25:49.000 --> 25:51.142
He died so that we might live.

25:51.863 --> 25:53.124
And then he rose from the grave.

25:53.565 --> 25:54.706
He's alive today.

25:55.202 --> 25:58.787
And so Jesus isn't just a historical figure that we look back on.

25:59.207 --> 26:01.490
He's a living savior that we can know.

26:01.510 --> 26:02.972
He's with us.

26:03.913 --> 26:07.438
Our joy comes from Him and He's alive.

26:08.219 --> 26:11.103
So our source of joy is unending.

26:11.243 --> 26:12.424
It's abundant.

26:13.225 --> 26:22.898
So I want to call you today to look to Jesus and trust in Him, especially knowing that trusting in Christ in hard times

26:23.394 --> 26:27.098
produces perseverance and endurance and growth in our lives.

26:28.279 --> 26:39.051
I'll give you an example of how hardship is a way that God often gets our attention and works in our lives in ways like we might not ever expect otherwise.

26:39.732 --> 26:42.315
There was a man in the 16th century named Ignatius.

26:42.375 --> 26:49.662
He lived in Spain and Ignatius growing up was just, how do I describe it?

26:50.003 --> 26:51.044
He was a real playboy.

26:51.665 --> 26:52.946
He was a womanizer.

26:53.026 --> 26:53.827
He was a fighter.

26:53.887 --> 26:55.068
He'd go and pick fights.

26:55.088 --> 26:56.249
He was real into fashion.

26:56.429 --> 26:59.752
He cared so much about his reputation and fame.

27:00.153 --> 27:02.235
Ignatius was a playboy.

27:02.255 --> 27:09.882
And yet he was in the military and one day in a battle, his right leg was struck by a cannonball.

27:10.323 --> 27:12.565
And this cannonball just shattered his leg.

27:13.285 --> 27:22.194
And so he had to go to the hospital and there they tried to set his leg and then they had to re-break it and set it again.

27:22.306 --> 27:26.452
He went into this season of immense suffering and isolation.

27:26.472 --> 27:28.114
He was bedridden.

27:28.154 --> 27:30.778
He was basically quarantined for this time.

27:30.798 --> 27:47.282
And after a while of being in this situation and just suffering and being miserable with nothing to do, he started reading a book about the life of Jesus and seeing who Jesus was and what he did for us.

27:48.226 --> 27:57.582
He experienced this incredible transformation in his life as he lay there, suffering his legs shattered by a cannonball.

27:57.602 --> 28:10.926
And yet it was this hardship that led to a transformation that completely changed the trajectory of his life, where he went from that point forward and lived for Jesus and lived to show others the glory of Jesus.

28:11.968 --> 28:13.330
And so I want to remind you,

28:13.730 --> 28:18.195
that God is at work not in spite of our hardship, but through our hardship.

28:18.856 --> 28:20.699
That's true of your life.

28:21.980 --> 28:22.661
God is at work.

28:22.761 --> 28:24.423
It's true for us as a church.

28:24.743 --> 28:27.186
We can be strengthened by this adversity.

28:28.848 --> 28:43.186
And so when we look to Christ and we remember all that He's done for us, it's then that we can have this kind of faith that can look even death in the face and not be afraid.

28:43.810 --> 28:50.198
And we too will be able to say like the Apostle Paul, to live is Christ, to die is gain.

28:50.859 --> 28:51.540
Let's pray together.

28:53.482 --> 29:09.703
God, we thank you that through the gospel, even death has been defeated so that while there is much suffering and hardship in this life, we don't need to be driven by our fear because we can look to Christ in faith.

29:11.225 --> 29:12.306
God, I pray that

29:12.834 --> 29:27.496
For anyone right now who's hearing this, who doesn't know you as Lord and Savior, I pray, God, that hearing of death and sickness and experiencing loss in their lives, I pray that they would look to you in this moment and say, Jesus, I trust you.

29:28.498 --> 29:29.760
I give you my life.

29:30.781 --> 29:34.006
I acknowledge that you died from my sins, that you rose from the grave.

29:35.388 --> 29:38.573
God, I pray that you would give them the faith to trust in you and that you would save them.

29:40.055 --> 29:41.938
Lord, I pray for every single one of us,

29:42.722 --> 29:59.525
that you would increase our faith in these hard times, to look to Jesus, to live for Him, to live in the tension of fruitful labor, to keep striving, to keep going and trusting in you, knowing that you are at work in all of this.

30:00.085 --> 30:01.127
We believe that, Lord.

30:01.808 --> 30:03.810
And we live for you, for your glory.

30:04.011 --> 30:06.514
We pray this in Jesus' name, amen.

